00:49:50,040 --> 00:49:54,639
but finally the team is allowed to begin
their journey to the hunters' camp.

431
00:49:54,640 --> 00:49:57,919
With no roads, sometimes the only
passable route is over

432
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:01,120
the fast melting
surfaces of the lakes.

433
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:12,760
OK?

434
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:19,640
They need to be
prepared for a quick exit.

435
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:31,399
The next day the crew finally
reach the coast.

436
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:33,960
The hunting camp is now
just 30 miles away

437
00:50:33,961 --> 00:50:36,519
across a bay, but the
crossing could be risky.

438
00:50:36,520 --> 00:50:41,320
The frozen sea is melting
fast in the spring sunshine.

439
00:50:46,560 --> 00:50:49,679
Confident it's safe? It's not going
to break underneath us?

440
00:50:49,680 --> 00:50:52,519
Is that the decision, 50/50?

441
00:50:52,520 --> 00:50:54,639
50/50!

442
00:50:54,640 --> 00:50:57,999
The locals employ several generations
of arctic transport,

443
00:50:58,000 --> 00:51:00,600
from the ancient to the merely
antique.

444
00:51:04,920 --> 00:51:09,479
With the sea ice cracking up beneath
them, Dan has to trust the crew

